# Vercel KV (Upstash Redis) REST credentials — the channel the laptop hands the
# Fyers refresh_token to the always-on cloud routine.
#
# SETUP (laptop): copy this file to mcp/.kv.env (drop the .example) and paste your
# two keys below. The file is gitignored — your keys never leave the laptop.
#
# WHERE TO GET THE KEYS:
#   vercel.com -> your portfolio-tracker project -> Storage tab -> open your
#   KV / Upstash Redis store -> the ".env.local" (or "API") section lists exactly
#   these two. If there's no store yet, click "Create Database" -> "Upstash for
#   Redis" (free), connect it to the project, then copy the keys.
#
# (The cloud Remote workspace gets these as env vars instead — same names.)

KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
